            </div><h2 id="what-is-mpd-" class="headerLink">
    <a href="#what-is-mpd-" class="header-mark"></a>What is mpd ?</h2><p>MPD (Music Player Daemon) is an audio player, used to play audio tracks, organize playlists with some database for musics. In order to interface with it, a client is needed (in our case (ncmpcpp)[https://rybczak.net/ncmpcpp/] is used).</p>
<h2 id="installation" class="headerLink">
    <a href="#installation" class="header-mark"></a>Installation</h2><ul>
<li>Install mpd and ncmpcpp on ArchLinux : <code>sudo pacman -S mpd ncmpcpp</code></li>
<li>Install mpDris2 (provides MPRIS 2 support to mpd): <code>yay -S mpdris2</code></li>
</ul>
